00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:20,080
And one check-in gets absorbed into the system at a time.

690
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:27,410
Then you go, hey, it's a lot easier to create a mechanism.

691
00:40:28,450 --> 00:40:36,370
Let's say you want to – some teams want to have a staging or a test environment before they go to prod.

692
00:40:37,730 --> 00:40:42,450
You create a system that says, okay, let's do one check-in at a time.

693
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:45,650
Let's validate goodness.

694
00:40:46,850 --> 00:40:50,610
I think – and a little bit of a rant here, but it falls into the principle.

695
00:40:51,570 --> 00:41:00,620
I think too many teams use Scrum as – one, incorrectly, and they think they're doing Agile.

696
00:41:01,580 --> 00:41:06,660
But what they're – they're focusing on iteration versus adaptability.

697
00:41:07,620 --> 00:41:15,890
The other value add – so when people say we want a hybrid between

698
00:41:16,290 --> 00:41:23,360
waterfall and Agile, one of the learnings that I've done is I've actually realized that Scrum

699
00:41:24,350 --> 00:41:27,230
is not Agile. Scrum is actually that hybrid.

700
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:33,860
Because what you want is – the problem with waterfall is –

701
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:43,140
Scrum has turned into – the idea of Scrum is that if the item's not complete,

702
00:41:43,140 --> 00:41:45,940
it's fine. It goes back into the backlog at the end of the sprint.

703
00:41:45,940 --> 00:41:51,060
But people feel bad not completing their commitment, so they shove them in at the end

704
00:41:51,060 --> 00:41:56,990
and create waterfall out of Scrum. Scrum as designed, I don't think, is the hybrid.

705
00:41:56,990 --> 00:42:02,670
What Scrum has grown largely into on, I would say, most teams following Scrum is exactly that.

706
00:42:04,740 --> 00:42:05,940
And I disagree.

707
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:07,860
Well, one of us is right.

708
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:09,700
Oh, well, good.

709
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:12,500
And one of us can edit out the I disagree part of the problem.

710
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:22,240
But it's not – that is spawning – I mean, that can be episode 93.

711
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:26,080
What else do you want to hit on this?

